# Trivy ignore list — accepted / triaged vulnerabilities.
#
# Add a CVE ID on its own line ONLY after triage, with a comment explaining
# why it is accepted (not exploitable in our context) and/or a review date.
# Prefer fixing (rebuild image, bump dependency) over ignoring.
#
# The CI gate uses `--ignore-unfixed`, so vulnerabilities without an upstream
# fix do not need to be listed here; this file is for *fixable* findings we are
# consciously deferring.
#
# Format:
#   CVE-2026-XXXXX   # reason — owner — review-by YYYY-MM-DD
#
# (intentionally empty — nothing accepted yet)
